Vice President Mike Pence spoke with High Representative of the European Union Federica Mogherini to discuss the Western Balkans and North Korea. Pence thanked Mogherini for her leadership on the Western Balkans and expressed the US' desire to work with the EU to advance the Euro-Atlantic aspirations of the countries in the region. He also welcomed the EU's support on North Korea and expressed the US' desire to coordinate next steps with allies and partners. Both leaders highlighted the enduring strength of the US-EU relationship and looked forward to future cooperation on shared challenges.